description:
## What
Change PaymentAction::Request and PaymentAction::Sent to carry amount_zatoshi: u64. Update every call site so the workspace compiles cleanly.

## Core type change (core/src/messages.rs)
- PaymentAction::Request { chain: Chain, amount: String }  →  { chain: Chain, amount_zatoshi: u64 }
- PaymentAction::Sent { chain: Chain, tx_hash: String, amount: String }  →  { chain: Chain, tx_hash: String, amount_zatoshi: u64 }
- Update the test at ~line 175: amount: "0.1".to_string() → amount_zatoshi: 10_000_000

## cli/src/commands.rs call sites (identified by INVENTORY)
1. Line ~2058: PaymentAction::Request { chain, amount: amount_str.to_string() }
   → { chain, amount_zatoshi: parse_zec_to_zatoshi(amount_str).map_err(|e| format!("invalid amount: {e}"))? }
2. Line ~1895: PaymentAction::Sent { ..., amount: amount.clone() } where amount = zatoshi_to_zec_string(...)
   → { ..., amount_zatoshi: session.amount_zatoshi }  (use the session's zatoshi value directly)
3. Line ~2840: PaymentAction::Sent { ..., amount: amount_str }
   → { ..., amount_zatoshi: amount_zatoshi_value }  (use the u64 variable directly)
4. Line ~2598 (resync Payer/Requested): PaymentAction::Request { ..., amount: zatoshi_to_zec_string(s.amount_zatoshi) }
   → { ..., amount_zatoshi: s.amount_zatoshi }
5. Line ~2618 (resync Payer/Sent): PaymentAction::Sent { ..., amount: zatoshi_to_zec_string(s.amount_zatoshi) }
   → { ..., amount_zatoshi: s.amount_zatoshi }
6. Line ~2997 destructure: if let PaymentAction::Request { chain, amount } = action
   → if let PaymentAction::Request { chain, amount_zatoshi } = action
   Remove the parse_zec_to_zatoshi call that follows; dust check becomes: if amount_zatoshi < DUST_THRESHOLD

## tui/src/event.rs call sites
1. Line ~1336: PaymentAction::Request { chain, amount: zatoshi_to_zec_string(amount_zatoshi) }
   → { chain, amount_zatoshi }  (variable is already u64)
2. Line ~687 destructure: PaymentAction::Request { chain, amount }
   → PaymentAction::Request { chain, amount_zatoshi }
   Change parse_zec_to_zatoshi call → use amount_zatoshi directly
   Display: format!("... {} ZEC", zatoshi_to_zec_string(amount_zatoshi))
3. Line ~726 destructure: PaymentAction::Sent { tx_hash, amount, .. }
   → { tx_hash, amount_zatoshi, .. }
   Display: format!("... {} ZEC ...", zatoshi_to_zec_string(amount_zatoshi))

## bot/src/dispatcher.rs
1. Line ~59: if let PaymentAction::Request { chain, amount } = action
   → if let PaymentAction::Request { chain, amount_zatoshi } = action
   The BotEvent::PaymentRequest has amount: String — convert: amount: zatoshi_to_zec_string(amount_zatoshi)

## Defensive programming
- At the incoming PaymentAction::Request destructure in cli (line ~2997): dust_threshold check uses the u64 directly, no parse call needed
- No unwrap() added
- BotEvent retains amount: String — convert with zatoshi_to_zec_string at the dispatcher only
- Do not change relay code (relay/src/ws.rs) — relay never deserializes ClearMessage

## Compile check
cargo build --workspace must succeed at the end of this bead.
